-- Reds Manager Dusty Baker Gets Two-Year Extension After Winning Division
-- B y   J a y   B e b e r m a n
-- 2010-10-04T18:26:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-04/reds-manager-dusty-baker-gets-two-year-extension-after-winning-division.html
The Cincinnati Reds have given
manager Dusty Baker a two-year contract extension through the
2012 season, the Major League Baseball team said in a statement.  The Reds won the National League Central Division with a
record of 91 wins and 71 losses, earning their first playoff
appearance since 1995.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jay Beberman at 
 jbeberman@bloomberg.net  